Anyway the code in tmux that spits out the escape sequence is doing something like

```
		bufferevent_write(wp->event, "\033]52;;", 6);
```

Xterm apparently defaults to 's0' if this field is empty, St just sets both the clipboard and selection buffers. Haven't investigated other terminals.

The relevant code in Alacritty is in alacritty_terminal/src/ansi.rs:

```
            b"52" => {
                if params.len() < 3 || params[1].is_empty() {
                    return unhandled(params);
                }

                match params[2] {
                    b"?" => self.handler.write_clipboard(params[1][0], writer),
                    base64 => self.handler.set_clipboard(params[1][0], base64),
                }
            },
```

Relevant code in xterm:

```
	if (*base == '\0')
	    base = "s0";
```

